# GitHub-Compatible Mermaid Diagrams

## Gantt Charts
```mermaid
gantt
    dateFormat  YYYY-MM-DD
    title       Example Progress
    excludes    weekends
    
    section Phase 1
    Task 1 :done, 2024-03-29, 1d
    Task 2 :done, 2024-03-29, 1d
    
    section Phase 2
    Task 3 :active, 2024-03-30, 7d
    Task 4 :2024-04-06, 14d
```

Key points:
- Use simple date-based tasks instead of dependencies
- Include `excludes weekends`
- Status indicators: `:done`, `:active` (no `:wait` or `:planned`)
- Simple sections without complex nesting
- Explicit dates for all tasks

## Pie Charts
```mermaid
pie showData
    title Example Distribution
    "Category A" : 30
    "Category B" : 20
    "Category C" : 50
```

Key points:
- Always use `showData` for better readability
- Keep titles and labels simple
- Use quotes for category names with spaces

## Flow Diagrams
```mermaid
graph LR
    subgraph Group1
        A["Node A<br/>Detail 1<br/>Detail 2"]
        B["Node B<br/>Detail 1<br/>Detail 2"]
    end
    
    subgraph Group2
        C["Node C<br/>Detail 1<br/>Detail 2"]
    end

    style Group1 fill:#ffcccc,stroke:#ff0000
    style Group2 fill:#ccffcc,stroke:#00ff00
```

Key points:
- Use `graph LR` or `graph TD` for direction
- HTML line breaks with `<br/>`
- Subgraphs for grouping
- Style definitions after nodes
- Quote text with spaces/special chars

## Best Practices
1. Test complex diagrams in [Mermaid Live Editor](https://mermaid.live) first
2. Keep diagrams simple and focused
3. Use HTML breaks instead of complex formatting
4. Prefer explicit dates over relative dependencies
5. Use emojis and colors for visual indicators
6. Include legends or keys for complex diagrams

## Common Issues
1. Avoid:
   - Complex task dependencies in Gantt charts
   - Nested subgraphs more than one level deep
   - Special characters in node IDs
   - Unsupported diagram types (quadrantChart, etc.)
   
2. Always use:
   - Simple, clear node names
   - Basic formatting
   - Explicit styling
   - Standard direction indicators (LR, TD, etc.) 